{
  "text": "RIP and qde3 ko . The mutants in the his-3 background were used as the host strains for his-3-targeting constructs. Culture conditions were the same as those described previously (1), by inoculating mycelium mats in shaking flasks with 50 ml medium. For liquid cultures containing quinic acid (QA), 0.01 M QA (pH 5.8) was added to the liquid culture medium containing 1\u03eb Vogel's medium, 0.1% glucose, and 0.17% arginine [CITATION_1] . The cultures were grown in the presence of QA for 2 days unless otherwise indicated. For liquid cultures containing histidine, a final concentration of 0.5 mg/ml was used.",
